HTML Structure:

```html
<div class="card-container">
  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Title 1</h2>
    <img src="img1.jpg" alt="Image 1">
    <p class="card-content">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Title 2</h2>
    <img src="img2.jpg" alt="Image 2">
    <p class="card-content">Suspendisse viverra ante felis, sit amet scelerisque magna tincidunt non.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h2 class="card-title">Title 3</h2>
    <img src="img3.jpg" alt="Image 3">
    <p class="card-content">Pellentesque sed erat viverra, pretium mi eget, vulputate justo.</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

CSS Styles:

```css
/* Card container */
.card-container {
  display: flex; /* Displays cards in a row by default */
  flex-wrap: wrap; /* Enables cards to drop to next row when necessary */
  justify-content: center; /* Centers the cards horizontally */
  gap: 20px; /* Adds 20px spacing between cards */
}

/* Each card */
.card {
  flex: 0 0 calc(33.33% - 20px); /* Sets
